@node "Intro" "  INTRODUCTION    "
@toc "Contents"
 CHRISP - an integrated signal/sample processor.
 ------------------------------------------------
  It can process in 8,16 or 32 bits, with the ability to perform real-time
processing on incoming signals (ie from parallel port sampler). Output and
input from any process, real-time or not, can be directed to any buffer -
that of another process, or of an IO port, thus allowing for chained effect
streams or multi-computer processing.

(The current version does NOT support redirectable linking, as the involved
protocols are not yet free of bugs.)

   Supported Formats
   -----------------

CHRISP currently supports 8-bit samples only.

Please @{"contactĀme" link "feedback" 0} if you have information concerning file formats for other
types of samples.


   Supported Equipment
   -------------------

Signed and unsigned 8-bit parallel port sampling is now complete, but not
included in the program.

Please @{"contactĀme" link "feedback" 0} if you have any kind of information whatsoever
concerning:
  -MIDI sample dumping
  -AudioCD direct sample transfers
  -Delfina DSP
  -Tocatta 16
  -The AHI library
  -Anything else that you might think that can be useful, such as example
code, suggestions etc
@endnode

@node "Requir" "  REQUIREMENTS    "
@toc "Contents"
     Minimum Requirements
     --------------------

  -OS 2.04+  (tested only under OS 3.0, but should work...)
  -1MB RAM
  -The mathxxx.library files in your libs: directory


      Suggested system
      ----------------

  -68020 upwards
  -4MB+ Fast Ram
  -ECS\AGA or (even better) Gfx board - Please use a promotor for this
program!
@endnode

@node "install" "  INSTALLATION    "
@toc "Contents"
            Installation
            ------------

   There is only one file. Double-click on it and hey, presto!

If there are problems, make sure that you have all the mathxxxx.library
files in your libs: directory.
@endnode

@node "featu" "    FEATURES      "
@toc "Contents"
               FEATURES
               --------

The list of existing features. The list is due to grow (see @{"future" link "future" 0})



   Effects Menu
   ------------


Effects:

   @{"GRUNGEĀĀĀĀĀĀ" link "GRUNGE" 0} 
   @{"FLANGEĀĀĀĀĀĀ" link "FLANGE" 0}
   @{"SUSTAINĀĀĀĀĀ" link "SUSTAIN" 0} 
   @{"OVERDRIVEĀĀĀ" link "OVERDRIVE" 0}   

Special Attributes:

   @{"OVERSAMPLING" link "OVERSAMPLING" 0}
   @{"MODULATE" link "MODULATE" 0}
   @{"32-bits" link "32-bits" 0}



   Filters Menu
   ------------


The filters menu is splitted into two categories: Frequency filters and
noise filters. The window also features two sliders. The frequency filters
only make use of the frequency slider, while the noise filters are
controlled from the sensitivity slider. The three butttons AddSpike AddNoise
and Analyse do nothing useful. I just put them there to test a few filters
and didn't want to bother with removing them. Note also that the filters
window will change look in the next version, the listviews will be larger
and each filtering process will open its own window.

Implemented filters:

   @{"CPDĀFilterĀ" link "CPD Filter" 0}
   @{"WhiteĀNoise" link "White Noise" 0}
@endnode

@node "use" "     USAGE        "
@toc "Contents"
               USAGE
               -----

Startup

  After you start the program, a requester appears asking you wether to open
on a new custom screen or on workbench. The default custom screen is a hires
interlaced PAL scren (640x512) with 8 colours. Public screens are not
supported yet.

Getting things Done

  Once your screen has been chosen, 3 windows appear: the waveform window,
the menu window and the play/edit window. The sample waveform appears in the
waveform window. In order to test some of the effects, you can either click
on LOAD or NEW button in the main menu window to load an existing sample or
create a new one. Note that currently only IFF 8SVX files (8-bit Amiga) are
supported. If you try to load up an unkown file it will be loaded as raw.
Use the requester to identify the correct format. The sample is loaded in
the default sample bank. New sounds can be created in any bank - Banks
currently use 8 bits.


The Play\Edit window is used to control the playback and storage of sound.
Click on Play to play the sound. Use the period gadget to change the
playback period. No editing functions are implemented yet, but the existing
multiple sample framework, (which is to be extended to 32 bits) will allow
complex editing/mixing.


Clicking on the Effects gadget, the effects window appears. All the enabled
effects open up their own window where their parameters may be adjusted. At
this time, effects can only be 'effected' on the WHOLE of the default sample
bank.


Clicking on the Filters gadget, the filters window appears. There exist two
list views. Select an appropriate filter and click on its corresponding
gadget (there are two gadgets. One for noise filters and one for frequency
filters). Use the Frequency slider to control the frequency range of the
frequency filter and the Sensitivity slider to adjust the noise filter's
sensitivity. Frequency sliders sometimes, but not always, have an effect on
noise filters too. Ignore the AddSpike,AddNoise,Analyse gadgets.



There were a few @{"bugs" link "bugs" 0} in the program. One of them is that no default value
exists for some parameters until the corresponding slider is moved. These
bugs should have been corrected now but since there is a chance that one or
two might have escaped me, please @{"informĀme" link "feedback" 0}.
@endnode

@node "future" "     FUTURE       "
@toc "Contents"
            The FUTURE
            ----------

After rewriting of all the routines in assembler for both 16 and 32 bit
processing, the following will be implemented, in order of priority:

   -Full support for multiple samples, or multi-channel samples (ie stereo)
and the necessary editing features.
   -Full support for 4,8,12,16,20,24-bit formats.
   -Real-time effects and mixing.
   -Effect linking and IO multi-routing.
   -Support for all known sound formats*
   -Datatype support*
   -AHI support*
   -MIDI sample dumping*
   -Direct Audio CD sampling (SCSI and\or ATAPI)*
   -Special GUI editor for linking multiple effects and IO ports.
   -Improvements on and additions to existing effects.
    Possible additions are:
      -Raytraced echoes
      -Doppler effects
      and all the other effects that are currently disabled. :)

(*)@{i}The author does not have the necessary documentation and is thus unable
to implement this feature, without @{b}@{ui} @{"YOURĀHELP!" link "feedback" 0}



NOTE:If you have any further suggestions, or any questions, @{"contactĀme" link "feedback" 0}.
Alright?@{ub}
@endnode

